<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06252</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT MANDATING ELECTION SPENDING LIMITS, DETERMINING ELECTION CONTRIBUTION LIMITS, AND ADJUSTING THEM PERIODICALLY BASED ON THE CURRENT INFLATION RATE AND THE CONSUMER PRICE INDEX</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Mandating Election Spending Limits, Determining Election Contribution Limits, And Adjusting Them Periodically Based On The Current Inflation Rate And The Consumer Price Index</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Mandates that COMELEC, in coordination with NEDA and PSA to periodically adjust the amount provided by law as the maximum allowable spending limits of any candidate or political party  based on the current inflation rate and the consumer price index; promulgate the maximum election spending and contributions limits and for every election not less than three (3) months from the start of every election campaign period; and issue the rules and regulations necessary to implement this Act.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Reasonable Election Spending Contribution Limits Act.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>GARCIA, PABLO JOHN F., FERRER, JULIET MARIE DE LEON, ORTEGA, PABLO C., PANOTES, MARISOL C., TALLADO, JOSEFINA B., VELOSO, VICENTE III &quot;CHING&quot; S.E.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-02-11</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Romualdez (F.M.) (000 2020-03-10)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITTEE REPORT NO.&nbsp00227</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBMITTED ON 2020-02-11</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBMITTED BY:&nbspSUFFRAGE AND ELECTORAL REFORMS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>RECOMMENDATIONS:&nbspApproval in substitution of House Bill Numbered 3090</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBSTITUTED BILLS